25/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO's Senior Military Representative to Macedonia Maj Gen Bernardo Alvarez del Manzano says the government is capable of dealing with all security problems that might arise. Del Manzano and other NATO officials met on Tuesday (24 June) with Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski, and stressed that from the military point of view, the country is stable.
In other news Tuesday, parliament decided to support proposed constitutional changes that would legalise wire-tapping as an action against organised crime. The measure, proposed by Interior Minister Hari Kostov, was defeated last month. This time it had the support of the main opposition party, VMRO-DPMNE. (Utrinski Vesnik - 25/06/03; MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 24/06/03)
